text:
FC is mostly lame. 

Who are some of the most followed CT personalities that aren't just CZ and big founders? People like Cobie or Ansem. 

Who are the most followed/"promoted" people on FC? You decide. 

Look at the difference in the content and posting of those people. FC would do well to push people more like Cobie and Ansem and not "thoughtfluencers" who're only really crypto people by accident.

cast.text:
i want to bring more of the CT meta to farcaster

the total difference of topics / content makes CT people feel farcaster is lame

text:
that‚Äôs a pretty surface level take.

the most followed / promoted people on FC are the ones who were earliest.

the majority of them are startup founders or builders, with full-time jobs or teams or families.

CT meta and memecoins require a ton of attention. to be good at it. you have to be locked in to it. 

but most of the large, early accounts on FC are busy building their own companies or families; they don‚Äôt have time to get in the weeds on the CT meta.

the best CT accounts are self-employed where the meta is a deep part of their job. it‚Äôs insanely impressive. i wish i could do it.

both are locked in, but on different things.

perhaps the most bullish path for the Farcaster ecosystem is to remain disconnected from CT culture, continue to build its own, and finally deliver on crypto‚Äôs promise of apps uniquely enabled by crypto rails that people actually want

This is a good take

Things make more sense when you see Farcaster as the self-selecting group of people that:

1) have wallets installed and know how to use them
2) are not cynical about crypto (aka the economic internet)

CT has 1 but not 2, and bsky has neither
